{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, the-- the Dutch Nazi-- you know, the Dutch police and the Nazis went into the ghetto and started beating up the Jews, so the ghetto organized.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of the men had started beating up the Dutch Nazis, and they chased them out of the ghetto, out of the streets.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It wasn't the ghetto like it was in Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was sort of certain streets, OK?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they chased them out of there, so then the German police had to come and-- to the aid of the-- the Dutch Nazis.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they, in order to-- as a warning, they picked up, I don't know, a couple of hundred-- I think 200 young Dutch Jews and sent them to Mauthausen, and they were killed in Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think that's how I knew about Mauthausen, because word got around, you know, what-- what-- what was happening.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, when I started going to the school, at the beginning there were about 80 kids there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Might have been a few less, but between 60 and 80 kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And every week there were less, OK?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, there were two reasons for this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One reason, some parents did go into hiding with their children, and some got picked up, you know, by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Germans used to come at night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the bigger cities, they had to-- they called them razzias.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They used to sort of cordon off a certain area where they knew many Jews lived, at night, like close it off, and then go from apartment to apartment or house to house.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and whoever was Jewish was taken out and put in-- in a holding area, and then taken to Westerbork which was a transit camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I knew about this, and I heard about this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Also, on another occasion, this must have been, I think, on the high holidays, 1942.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't think it was 1940.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It must have been 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was not-- not long before we went.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Dinxperlo was a very-- it was a small village, but it had a well-established Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Small, but well established.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were some wealthy Jews living there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were, for instance, two brothers called Prince who had a carpet factory where half the village worked there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they had huge houses, and I guess they supported the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They supported the community.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I remember that one of the Princes lived opposite us, had a big-- like a big yard where everybody-- all the kids used to play-- Jews or non-Jews used to play there, used to play football, soccer, you know, like you're playing. and we were friendly with them, you know.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we went to services on Erev Yom Kippur and [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I would say there may have been in-- in those days, I think, only men-- only the men went to-- to the synagogue, at least on [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't know many people were in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There must have been at least 30, 40.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe less-- you know, 20, whatever.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But at-- at least a good amount of people, OK?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the rumor spread that the Germans were coming to pick up the men and take them to Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's-- that's how I always-- Mauthausen always reminded me-- me of my-- my memory from those days, you know, for two reasons.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of the reasons, I heard about it before, and it was frightening.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was the threat, that everybody would be sent to Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the rumor was that on Yom Kippur evening they were going to be picked up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the rumor and the message got to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was evening, so the men one by one started to leave.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, they didn't want to be caught in the synagogue, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they left one by one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only people left in the end was the-- the hazzan, you knwo, the cantor, and my cousin and myself, OK?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then the cantor asks, why-- why-- why don't you leave?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, what are you doing here?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, you better go home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we left, and we went home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the threat at the time was that we'd be picked up and-- and sent to Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it could have been that the rumor came-- often the Germans planted rumors, you know, in order to, you know, frighten people and then do whatever they wanted to do,",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know whether it was a real threat, or whether it wasn't, but I know that's the last time I was in a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
